    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-18T23:56:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-18T23:56:00-05:00" n="525"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Lot 55D128: Black Book, Tab 47: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief, United Nations Command</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ridgway</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Joint Chiefs of
                            Staff</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-19T14:56:00+10:00">19
                            August 1951—2:56 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>C–69215. This msg in 3 parts. Subject is meeting of sub-delegation at Kaesong 19
                    Aug.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Part 1</hi>. Summary: Non productive session again today.
                    Hodes and Burke constituted sub-delegation. Hsieh did most enemy talking but
                    used same old arguments. They continue insist on 38th parallel as basis for all
                    lines and zones. We insisted military balance must be maintained and our ground
                    positions be defensible during period of armistice. Meetings continue
                    tomorrow.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Part 2</hi>. Progress: None.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Part 3</hi>. Conclusions: The <gloss target="#t_UNC1"
                        >UNC</gloss> delegation draws same conclusions as on 18 Aug. I concur.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
